alert.note: Alert for King (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued November 05 at 12:08PM PDT until November 05 at 7:27PM PDT by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Washington... Snoqualmie River Near Snoqualmie Falls affecting King County. .Heavy rain over the area has ended early Saturday morning. The Snoqualmie River crested early this morning and will continue to recede throughout today. ...FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Snoqualmie River Near Snoqualmie Falls. * WHEN...Until this evening. * IMPACTS...At 20,000.0 cfs, the Snoqualmie River will cause widespread flooding of pasture lands and roads along the river from the town of Snoqualmie downstream through Fall City. Roads that may become flooded include Fall City-Carnation...Tolt Hill... and Novelty Flats Roads. This river level on the Snoqualmie corresponds roughly to a phase 3 flood in the King County flood system. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 10:45 AM PDT Saturday the flow was 18,100.0 cfs. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage late this morning and continue falling to 2,400 cfs early Tuesday morning. - Flood flow is 20,000.0 cfs. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by this evening at 730 PM PDT.
